A family of great blue heron.

Suddenly commotion, shrieking. A female Red-winged Blackbird was chasing a Great Blue Heron. The Heron landed on a tree trunk and seemed to be perplexed, stunned. The female Blackbird picked at the Heron's back, then flew circles, and attacked its face. When also the male Blackbird went after the Heron, it took off, with the Blackbird in hot pursuit.
Perched on top of tree

I was focused on the female Ring-necked Duck from my previous observation, when I noticed something big approaching. I turned, refocused the camera, and got these two shots. And then the Heron disappeared behind trees. When I found the Heron on the other side of the pond, there wasn't much left of the Gopher...

Though most of are missing our Sunday brunches at present, this Great Blue Heron seems to have found the shrimp bar. I always watch them when they seem to be in a serious hunt mode and this time paid off  with the capture of a large crustacean.

A great blue heron hunting at the lakeshore on the island at Sepulveda Basin Wildlife Reserve.

Long, thin-beaked bird with skinny black legs and mostly brown feathers at Marina Del Rey docks. About 2-3 feet tall without its neck. Not a night heron; looks too big and has black, flamingo-like legs. Looks closer to a blue heron but i'm not sure and don't know if juvenile or adult, male or female.
